modules.description: Provides functions to manage job queues with specific actions, validate client connections based on socket addresses, log events with timestamps, and specify a temporary directory for job storage. Works with queue names, socket addresses, and string-based logging. Used to control access to a print server, track client activity, and manage temporary job files.

Handles socket communication with buffered I/O, supporting platforms where standard input channels are unavailable. Processes LPD events and executes custom-defined actions for print jobs. Implements a spooler for printing on Windows via GSPRINT, adhering to RFC 1179 specifications.

Provides functions to manage print queues, validate client connections, log activity with timestamps, and specify a temporary directory for job storage. Operates with queue configurations, socket addresses, and string-based logging. Used to control access to print services, track session activity, and manage job file persistence.
